tum mechanics. It maintains the work’s proven chapter structure with theory and application examples followed by an in-depth section. In addition to discussing uncorrelated and correlated identical particles, it offers detailed and clear explanations of the quantum theory of electromagnetic fields; atomic photon absorption, emission and scattering; and quantum entanglement.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh1 aDiu, Bernard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHenkel, Carsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaloë, Franck, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831106492150 cprintz978311062064140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311064913040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110649130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110649130/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPCb2020